1. React components are JavaScript/Typescript (Python, Kotlin) functions that return markup

```javascript
function MyButton() {
  return (
    <button>I'm a button</button>
  );
}
```

2.  Nesting components  

```javascript
export default function MyApp() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Welcome to my app</h1>
      <MyButton />
    </div>
  );
}
```

3. Convention

React component names must always start with a capital letter, while HTML tags must be lowercase.

1. JSX is a syntax extension for JavaScript often used with React. 
2. It allows you to write HTML-like syntax directly in your JavaScript code. 
3. However, JSX has stricter rules than HTML, such as requiring self-closing tags like <br /> and requiring a single parent element for multiple JSX elements.  
4. To convert HTML to JSX, you can use online converters for convenience.  
    * [online converter](https://transform.tools/html-to-jsx)

```javascript
function AboutPage() {
  return (
    <>
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>Hello there.<br />How do you do?</p>
    </>
  );
}
```
